Nigeria president Muhammad Buhari on Sunday ordered a total lockdown of activities in two states and the capital city Abuja. The lockdown which began on Monday evening in  Abuja, and Lagos, which have the highest number of coronavirus cases in the country, and Ogun State which shares boundary with Lagos State, would have their residents staying at home for the next 14days. Our correspondents took a tour of major places of mass gatherings in the states on Tuesday and reported the level of compliance in pictures. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .